com.seagate.csp.gui.dlg.result

Class LocalResultFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.seagate.csp.gui.dlg.result.LocalResultFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Destroyable

    public class LocalResultFile
extends java.lang.Object
implements Destroyable
    Local representation of a result file. The object does not hold any data, so the clients must subscribe before starting the object. That forces only one possible listener per instance, so there's no need for proper add/remove listener infrastructure. The class is thread-safe and fully asynchronous. The event listener must re-route event calls to the event processing thread. The long ops, like make*() should be done via worker threads.
